HOWTO SET UP AN NFS-KERNEL-SERVER ON YOUR WORKSTATION
-----------------------------------------------------

1. install nfs-kernel-server

2. copy your Linux root file system to /export/rfs

4. add local IP address
> sudo ifconfig eth0:1 192.168.35.1

5. configure NFS kernel server
> sudo gedit /etc/exports
insert: "/exports 192.168.35.0/255.255.255.0(rw,insecure,no_root_squash,no_all_squash,no_subtree_check)"

6. restart NFS kernel server
sudo service nfs-kernel-server restart
